http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/Maoists-abduct-four-Maharashtra-students-in-Bastar/article13978755.ece

Four students from Maharashtra have been allegedly abducted by the Maoists in restive Bastar region of Chhattisgarh.The students, who were on a “cycle tour” of Maoist insurgency-hit area of Maharashtra-Chhattisgarh and Orrisa, went missing on December 29.According to some sources, the boys had entered Bastar through Bhatpar village in Gadchiroli–Bijapur district border and their last location was in Basaguda town of Bijapur district.A person based in Nagpur was informed about the alleged abductions through a phone call from Sukma district of Bastar on Saturday.Bastar Inspector-General of Police, S R P Kalluri said that he had heard of the news and had activated his informers to gather more information about the alleged abductions.“All possible efforts would be made to save the boys if they have been abducted in Bastar,” Mr.Kalluri told The Hindu.Two of the four boys have been identified as Adarsh and Vikas.